Recurrent prosthetic valve thrombosis: importance of prolonged Doppler echocardiography examination for diagnosis. In a 9-month period a 52-year-old woman was admitted on 3 occasions with thrombotic obstruction of a Medtronic Hall aortic valve prosthesis. On the first occasion the diagnosis was clinically obvious on the second occasion prosthetic valve malfunction was detected fortuitously on Doppler echocardiography